James Abraham, Jos The Minister of State for Industry, Trade and Investment, Maryam Katagum, has said Nigerian youths deserve better standard of living. She noted that that unemployment and under-employment still posed a challenge in the country. The minister spoke on Thursday at a Stakeholders Dialogue Forum and Outstanding Trainees Award ceremony organised by the Industrial Training Fund in conjunction with Nigeria Employers Consultative Association. The occasion which was hosted virtually by the ITF at its headquarters in Jos was joined by more than thirty organisations and several ITF state offices across the country  as well representatives from the Federal Ministries  of Education, Works and Youths among others. According to the minister,  throughout the presidency of the Buhari regime, the Federal Government has encouraged it’s agencies to engage in public private partnership to address the challenges facing the country. Copyright PUNCH.
